üöÄ Deployment Guide - Doc&Go Marketing Website
This guide covers deploying your Next.js 14 marketing site to various platforms.
üìã Pre-Deployment Checklist
Before deploying, ensure you've:
[ ] Tested locally with npm run build && npm start
[ ] Updated all placeholder content
[ ] Added real testimonials
[ ] Connected email form to backend/service
[ ] Added analytics (Google Analytics, Plausible, etc.)
[ ] Verified all links work
[ ] Tested on mobile devices
[ ] Run accessibility audit (Lighthouse)
[ ] Added privacy policy and terms of service pages
[ ] Set up error tracking (Sentry, LogRocket, etc.)
[ ] Optimized any images added
[ ] Updated SEO metadata in app/layout.tsx
üéØ Option 1: Vercel (Recommended)
Best for: Next.js sites (made by Next.js creators)
Why Vercel?
‚úÖ Zero configuration
‚úÖ Automatic deployments from Git
‚úÖ Global CDN
‚úÖ Free SSL certificates
‚úÖ Free tier available
‚úÖ Best performance for Next.js
Deploy via CLI
# Install Vercel CLI
npm i -g vercel

# Navigate to project
cd docandgo-marketing

# Deploy
vercel

# Follow prompts:
# - Link to existing project? No
# - Project name: docandgo-marketing
# - Directory: ./
# - Build command: [auto-detected]
Deploy via GitHub
Push code to GitHub repository
Go to vercel.com
Click "Add New Project"
Import your GitHub repository
Click "Deploy" (settings auto-detected)
Done! Site will be live at your-project.vercel.app
Custom Domain
In Vercel dashboard, go to project settings
Click "Domains"
Add your domain (e.g., docandgo.com)
Update DNS records as shown
Wait for DNS propagation (5-60 minutes)
üé® Option 2: Netlify
Best for: Ease of use, great free tier
Deploy via CLI
# Install Netlify CLI
npm install -g netlify-cli

# Build the project
npm run build

# Deploy
netlify deploy

# For production:
netlify deploy --prod
Deploy via GitHub
Push code to GitHub
Go to netlify.com
Click "Add new site" ‚Üí "Import from Git"
Select your repository
Configure build settings:
Build command: npm run build
Publish directory: .next
Click "Deploy site"
Custom Domain
In Netlify dashboard, go to "Domain settings"
Click "Add custom domain"
Follow DNS configuration instructions
‚òÅÔ∏è Option 3: AWS Amplify
Best for: AWS ecosystem integration
Deploy via Console
Go to AWS Amplify Console
Click "New app" ‚Üí "Host web app"
Connect your Git provider (GitHub, GitLab, etc.)
Select repository and branch
Build settings (auto-detected):
version: 1
frontend:
  phases:
    preBuild:
      commands:
        - npm ci
    build:
      commands:
        - npm run build
  artifacts:
    baseDirectory: .next
    files:
      - '**/*'
  cache:
    paths:
      - node_modules/**/*
Click "Save and deploy"
üî∂ Option 4: Cloudflare Pages
Best for: Performance and DDoS protection
Deploy via Dashboard
Push code to GitHub/GitLab
Go to Cloudflare Pages
Click "Create a project"
Connect Git repository
Configure build:
Build command: npm run build
Build output directory: .next
Click "Save and Deploy"
üê≥ Option 5: Docker + Any VPS
Best for: Full control, existing infrastructure
Create Dockerfile
FROM node:18-alpine AS deps
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci

FROM node:18-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules
COPY . .
RUN npm run build

FROM node:18-alpine AS runner
WORKDIR /app
ENV NODE_ENV production
RUN addgroup --system --gid 1001 nodejs
RUN adduser --system --uid 1001 nextjs

COPY --from=builder /app/public ./public
COPY --from=builder --chown=nextjs:nodejs /app/.next/standalone ./
COPY --from=builder --chown=nextjs:nodejs /app/.next/static ./.next/static

USER nextjs
EXPOSE 3000
ENV PORT 3000

CMD ["node", "server.js"]
Update next.config.js
module.exports = {
  output: 'standalone',
  reactStrictMode: true,
}
Build and Run
# Build image
docker build -t docandgo-marketing .

# Run container
docker run -p 3000:3000 docandgo-marketing
üñ•Ô∏è Option 6: Traditional VPS (DigitalOcean, Linode, etc.)
Best for: Existing server infrastructure
Prerequisites
Ubuntu 22.04+ VPS
Domain pointed to server IP
SSH access
Setup
# SSH into server
ssh user@your-server-ip

# Install Node.js
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

# Install PM2
sudo npm install -g pm2

# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/docandgo-marketing.git
cd docandgo-marketing

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Build
npm run build

# Start with PM2
pm2 start npm --name "docandgo" -- start
pm2 save
pm2 startup
Nginx Reverse Proxy
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name docandgo.com www.docandgo.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}
SSL with Let's Encrypt
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx
sudo certbot --nginx -d docandgo.com -d www.docandgo.com
üìä Post-Deployment
1. Verify Deployment
[ ] Visit your live URL
[ ] Test all interactive elements
[ ] Submit email form
[ ] Check mobile responsiveness
[ ] Test all navigation links
[ ] Verify analytics tracking
2. Monitor Performance
Use these tools:
PageSpeed Insights: https://pagespeed.web.dev
GTmetrix: https://gtmetrix.com
WebPageTest: https://www.webpagetest.org
3. Set Up Monitoring
Uptime monitoring: UptimeRobot, Pingdom
Error tracking: Sentry, Rollbar
Analytics: Google Analytics, Plausible
4. Security Headers
Add these headers in your hosting platform:
X-Frame-Options: DENY
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
For Vercel, create vercel.json:
{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "X-Frame-Options",
          "value": "DENY"
        },
        {
          "key": "X-Content-Type-Options",
          "value": "nosniff"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
üîß Environment Variables
If you add backend integration:
Local Development
Create .env.local:
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
Production
Add to your hosting platform:
Vercel: Project Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
Netlify: Site Settings ‚Üí Environment
AWS: Amplify Console ‚Üí Environment Variables
üö® Troubleshooting
Build Fails
# Clear cache and rebuild
rm -rf .next
rm -rf node_modules
npm install
npm run build
Site Not Loading
Check build logs in hosting dashboard
Verify domain DNS settings (use dig or nslookup)
Check SSL certificate status
Review server logs
Performance Issues
Enable Next.js Image Optimization
Add next/font for font optimization
Implement code splitting
Enable compression on server
üìà Optimization Tips
1. Enable Caching
In next.config.js:
module.exports = {
  async headers() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/static/:path*',
        headers: [
          {
            key: 'Cache-Control',
            value: 'public, max-age=31536000, immutable',
          },
        ],
      },
    ];
  },
}
2. Add Sitemap
Create app/sitemap.ts:
export default function sitemap() {
  return [
    {
      url: 'https://docandgo.com',
      lastModified: new Date(),
    },
  ]
}
3. Add robots.txt
Create app/robots.ts:
export default function robots() {
  return {
    rules: {
      userAgent: '*',
      allow: '/',
    },
    sitemap: 'https://docandgo.com/sitemap.xml',
  }
}
